<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What a weird job John Ray has. I suppose that =
in general, if a company hires a new chief executive officer, the new CEO w=
ill have some disagreements with the previous CEO, and some incentive to ma=
ke a meal of those disagreements. For one thing, CEOs are generally people =
with strong opinions. Also the new CEO was hired for a reason; quite possib=
ly=C2=A0the old CEO did do something wrong. Also the new CEO can make himse=
lf look better by making the old one look worse: The more you say =E2=80=9C=
oh man the previous guy really messed everything up, what a disaster this p=
lace is,=E2=80=9D the more credit you will get for any improvements.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also I mean, separately, the former CEO of FTX=
 Trading Ltd. really did mess the place up a lot, so Ray objectively has a =
lot to complain about.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still it is hard to think of a CEO in recent m=
emory who has been more focused on trashing the previous management? (<a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31118652.257452/aHR0cHM=
6Ly93d3cubnByLm9yZy8yMDIyLzEyLzE0LzExNDI2NjYwNjcvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWlzLXVzaW5nLX=
RoZS10d2l0dGVyLWZpbGVzLXRvLWRpc2NyZWRpdC1mb2VzLWFuZC1wdXNoLWNvbnNwaXJhY3ktd=
Ghlb3I/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB55c88dd3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Elon Musk I guess</a>?)=
=C2=A0Ray was hired as the CEO of FTX to put it into bankruptcy, to steer i=
t through bankruptcy, and to maximize recovery for FTX=E2=80=99s customers =
and other creditors, and he has spent a lot of his time publishing gleeful =
reports about how bad everything at FTX is and how incompetent and criminal=
 its former managers, led by former CEO Sam Bankman-Fried, were. Obviously =
a lot of people =E2=80=94=C2=A0most notably US federal prosecutors, but als=
o FTX=E2=80=99s customers and, you know, journalists=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0ar=
e very interested in how incompetent and criminal those former managers wer=
e, and the reports are quite informative and I am glad he=E2=80=99s publish=
ing them. Still they are in a little bit of=C2=A0tension with Ray=E2=80=99s=
=C2=A0main<em>=C2=A0</em>job of maximizing recoveries. Occasionally Ray and=
 his team will make noises about how they might=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31118652.257452/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21i=
ZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDEtMTkvZnR4LWlzLXBsYW5uaW5nLWEtY29=
tZWJhY2s_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQxMDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc2=
91cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNDEwJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBac29762d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">restart FTX=E2=80=99s business</=
a>=C2=A0to earn money to pay off creditors, and then they=E2=80=99ll put ou=
t a report with a title like =E2=80=9CFTX Debtors Discover That FTX Was the=
 Worst Company in the History of Companies,=E2=80=9D and that doesn=E2=80=
=99t feel like=C2=A0great advertising?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or maybe it is? Maybe the way to win back trus=
t is to be very open about how bad things were before? But I am not sure wh=
ether the goal of these reports is to maximize the going-concern value of F=
TX=E2=80=99s business, or to explain why that=E2=80=99s hard, or just to ve=
nt about the problems of previous management.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway yesterday FTX <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31118652.257452/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucHJuZXdzd2l=
yZS5jb20vbmV3cy1yZWxlYXNlcy9mdHgtZGVidG9ycy1yZWxlYXNlLXJlcG9ydC1vbi1mdHgtZ3=
JvdXBzLWNvbnRyb2wtZmFpbHVyZXMtMzAxNzkyODkxLmh0bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
fc0e0cb1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;"> published another report</a> about its prior incompetenc=
e =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9CFTX Debtors Release Report on FTX Group's Control=
 Failures=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0and it is wild reading.<a class=3D"footno=
te-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: no=
ne !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bord=
er-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important;=
 display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0A lot of it is=C2=A0elaboration on stuff we already knew (in part=
 because Ray has <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
1118652.257452/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIw=
MjItMTEtMTcvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1mdHgtd2FzLW5vdC12ZXJ5LWNhcmV=
mdWw_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQxMDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cm=
NlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNDEwJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cB68d9aec5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  published previous reports about i=
t</a>): FTX was bad at keeping track of its accounts, it was bad at keeping=
 control of its crypto, it handed over lots of money to insiders in unexpla=
ined and poorly documented ways, and it let Alameda Research, Bankman-Fried=
=E2=80=99s trading firm, take a ton of risks with customer money in a way t=
hat <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31118652.25745=
2/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTItMTMva=
G93LXRvLWRvLWZyYXVkLWF0LWEtZnV0dXJlcy1leGNoYW5nZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNDEwMjNfTU9O=
RVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0=
yMzA0MTAmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBec653b0e"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">  ultimately bankrupted FTX</a>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still there are new anecdotes that I cannot re=
sist quoting. For instance, we knew that FTX=E2=80=99s accounting was bad, =
but here=E2=80=99s Bankman-Fried making that point himself:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In an internal communication, Bankman-Fried de=
scribed Alameda as =E2=80=9Chilariously beyond any threshold of any auditor=
 being able to even get partially through an audit,=E2=80=9D adding:</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CAlameda is unauditable. I don=E2=80=
=99t mean this in the sense of =E2=80=98a major accounting firm will have r=
eservations about auditing it=E2=80=99; I mean this in the sense of =E2=80=
=98we are only able to ballpark what its balances are, let alone something =
like a comprehensive transaction history.=E2=80=99 We sometimes find $50m o=
f assets lying around that we lost track of; such is life.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s statements evidence th=
e challenges a competent audit firm would have had to overcome to audit Ala=
meda=E2=80=99s business.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ha ha ha. Look, if you run a financial institu=
tion, and you=C2=A0sometimes finding an extra $50 million of assets lying a=
round, you might say things like =E2=80=9Cooh money=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Ct=
hat=E2=80=99s hilarious=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Csuch is life.=E2=80=9D Findin=
g money feels good! But it is indicative of a deeper problem. =E2=80=9CIf I=
 sometimes find $50 million of assets lying around that I lost track of,=E2=
=80=9D you might think in more reflective=C2=A0moments, =E2=80=9Cis it poss=
ible that I will sometimes find $50 million of<em> liabilities</em> lying a=
round that I lost track of?=E2=80=9D Because that would be bad. In the even=
t, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31118652.257452=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTQvZn=
R4LXMtYmFsYW5jZS1zaGVldC13YXMtYmFkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA0MTAyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0b=
V9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDQxMCZ1dG1f=
Y2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0ac1af08" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  FTX=
 was undone because</a>, and I cannot emphasize this strongly enough, IT FO=
UND $8 BILLION OF LIABILITIES LYING AROUND THAT IT LOST TRACK OF, whoops. B=
etter to keep track of all the money!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The report also objects to=C2=A0how FTX held o=
n to its crypto. Like any crypto exchange, FTX was in the business of holdi=
ng crypto for itself and its customers, and =E2=80=9Cholding crypto=E2=80=
=9D means basically keeping track of the private keys that allow you to acc=
ess your crypto. There are some best practices for this sort of thing, if y=
ou are holding a lot of crypto for customers: You try to keep most of it in=
 =E2=80=9Ccold wallets=E2=80=9D not connected to the internet, and you writ=
e down your private keys in ways that are (1) more permanent and secure tha=
n Post-It notes but also (2) less hackable than iPhone notes. FTX=E2=80=99s=
 new management says that FTX=E2=80=99s old management used mostly worst pr=
actices to hold on to customer crypto:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">FTX Group kept virtually all crypto assets in =
hot wallets, which are far more susceptible to hacking, theft, misappropria=
tion, and inadvertent loss than cold wallets because hot wallets are intern=
et-connected. Prudently-operated crypto exchanges keep the vast majority of=
 crypto assets in cold wallets, which are not connected to the internet, an=
d maintain in hot wallets only the limited amount necessary for daily opera=
tion, trading, and anticipated=C2=A0customer withdrawals.=C2=A0Relatedly, p=
rudently-operated crypto exchanges implement strict processes and controls =
to minimize the security risks (for example, the risk of hacking, theft or =
loss) inherent in the transfer of crypto assets between hot and cold wallet=
s.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The FTX Group undoubtedly recognized how a pru=
dent crypto exchange should operate, because when asked by third parties to=
 describe the extent to which it used cold storage, it lied. For example, i=
n 2019, Bankman-Fried falsely responded to a customer question on Twitter b=
y providing assurance that =E2=80=9C[we use the] standard hot wallet/cold w=
allet setup.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A general theme in the collapse of FTX is that=
 FTX was quite good at=C2=A0<em>sounding like=C2=A0</em>it was a good crypt=
o exchange. It knew how to say the right things, which created the impressi=
on that it was also doing them.=C2=A0In <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/31118652.257452/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vc=
GluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTItMDEvc2JmLW1pc3NlZC1mdHgtcy1yaXNrcz9jbXBpZD1C=
QkQwNDEwMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHR=
lciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA0MTAmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cB3903eccc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;">  proposals to regulators</a>, and in Bankman-Frie=
d=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/311186=
52.257452/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItM=
TItMDYveW91LWNhbi10LXRlbGwtYW5hbHlzdHMtdG9vLW11Y2g_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQxMDIzX01P=
TkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm0=
9MjMwNDEwJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB20a225af=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;">  Twitter account</a>, FTX regularly seemed to be thoughtful abou=
t managing the risks of a leveraged crypto futures exchange. FTX=E2=80=99s =
executives clearly=C2=A0<em>thought</em> about the right issues =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0liquidation of losing positions, hot wallet/cold wallet crypto storag=
e =E2=80=94=C2=A0and so it was natural to assume that they=C2=A0<em>did=C2=
=A0</em>something about them. Turns out, nope!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Debtors identified private keys to over $1=
00 million in Ethereum assets stored in plain text and without encryption o=
n an FTX Group server.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Debtors identified private keys, as well a=
s credentials to third-party exchanges, that enabled access to tens of mill=
ions of dollars in crypto assets that were stored in plain text and without=
 encryption across multiple servers from which they could be accessed by ma=
ny other servers and users in many locations.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Single-signature-based private keys to billion=
s of dollars in crypto assets were stored in AWS Secrets Manager (a cloud-b=
ased tool used to manage sensitive information), and/or a password vault (a=
 tool for secure storage of passwords), neither of which is designed to mee=
t the needs of secure-key storage; any of the many FTX Group employees who =
had access to AWS Secrets Manager or the password vault could access certai=
n of the keys and unilaterally transfer the corresponding assets.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know, is storing your secret p=
asswords in Amazon=E2=80=99s Secrets Manager a=C2=A0good practice or a bad =
one? I could see arguments either way. Also here=E2=80=99s this:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Alameda also lacked appropriate do=
cumentation as to the description or usage of private keys. For example, a =
key for $600 million dollars=E2=80=99 worth of crypto assets was titled wit=
h four non-descriptive words, and stored with no information about what the=
 key was for, or who might have relevant information about it. The Debtors =
identified other keys to millions of dollars in crypto assets that were sim=
ply titled =E2=80=9Cuse this=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cdo not use,=E2=80=9D with=
 no further context.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Incredibly relatable. Who among us has not sav=
ed our most precious data in a file titled =E2=80=9Cuse this one=E2=80=9D? =
This works, I guess, imperfectly, if your company is basically a half-dozen=
 friends in a suite in the Bahamas. But it=E2=80=99s not best practices, an=
d in particular, if the friends who run the company all get kicked out for =
incompetence and criminality and angry professionals come in to clean up th=
e mess, they will be very annoyed to find all the crypto stored like this.=
=C2=A0</p>
